data.text/latex:
\begin{verbatim}
agwn(x, snr_dB; rst = true)
\end{verbatim}
Adds a Gaussian White Noise (AGWN) to a signal \texttt{x} with a given SNR.

\textbf{Inputs}

\begin{itemize}
\item \texttt{x}: Signal (Real or Complex)


\item \texttt{snr\_dB}: signal to noise ratio [dB]


\item \texttt{rst}: Reset the random number generator - Bool

\end{itemize}
\textbf{Output}

\begin{itemize}
\item \texttt{y}: Noisy signal

\end{itemize}

\begin{verbatim}
acn(x, snr_dB, fs, color = :pink; band_freq = Float64[], rst = true)
\end{verbatim}
Adds a complex Colored Noise (ACN) to a signal \texttt{x} with a given SNR

\textbf{Inputs}

\begin{itemize}
\item \texttt{x}: Signal


\item \texttt{snr\_dB}: Signal to noise ratio [dB]


\item \texttt{fs}: Sampling frequency [Hz]


\item \texttt{color}: Color of the noise

\begin{itemize}
\item \texttt{:white}


\item \texttt{:pink} (default)


\item \texttt{:blue}


\item \texttt{:brown}


\item \texttt{:purple}

\end{itemize}

\item \texttt{band\_freq}: Frequencies used to defined the bandpass filter applied to the colored noise


\item \texttt{rst}: Reset the random number generator

\end{itemize}
\textbf{Output}

\begin{itemize}
\item \texttt{y}: Noisy signal

\end{itemize}

